		 <part part_index="3" name="Travel like Harry Potter" page="0" source="2">
      	<article allWordsNum="107">
            	<![CDATA[
Visitors to Norway (挪威) can now travel in the footsteps of Harry Potter. Parts of the movie Harry Potter and the Half-Blood Prince (《哈利•波特与混血王子》) were filmed on the train line Raumabanen (饶玛列车), between Oslo (奥斯陆) and the Norwegian fjord region (峡湾地区).
A trip on the train line gives you a unique opportunity to experience some of the most beautiful scenery in Norway. In only one hour, the train will take you from beautiful fjords to wild mountains.
Once you get on the train, all you need to do is sit back, look through the large windows and enjoy your journey.
Do you want to take the train and travel like Harry Potter?
  	]]>
            </article>
